subject: Re: [junit] Linkage Error
msgSnippet: On Wed, 2003-03-19 at 12:04, Mr james asher wrote: If you re referring to the Document.class file, no it is not included in any other jar on the classpath,
messageBody:
On Wed, 2003-03-19 at 12:04, Mr james asher wrote:

If you're referring to the Document.class file, no it
is not included in any other jar on the classpath,
other than the xml-apis.jar. The fact that I'm using
jwebunit on top of junit shouldn't have anything to do
with it, right?

I am replying with:

Not sure if jwebunit has anything to do with it or not. But it's a good
start. Also, what version of the JDK are you using? You may need to
bootstrap the xml-apis.jar...

=jason
